In a new Maya scene, I have added the scanned and conformed mesh obj files.

72
00:06:05.420 --> 00:06:12.060
Over here in the Outliner, this is the scanned mesh, which is what was used for the solve.

73
00:06:12.060 --> 00:06:18.180
Over here, I'm going to unhide the conformed mesh that was generated from the solve.

74
00:06:18.180 --> 00:06:24.139
Since this is already of metahuman topology, we can use this to refit accents that may

75
00:06:24.139 --> 00:06:30.259
have been lost during the solve while preserving the existing polygon flow.

76
00:06:30.259 --> 00:06:34.340
Let's do a quick review before we move on.

77
00:06:34.340 --> 00:06:39.740
The conformed mesh can be used to bring back volume and large accents that may have been

78
00:06:39.740 --> 00:06:45.220
lost in the solve while preserving the existing polygon flow.

79
00:06:45.220 --> 00:06:51.340
Just ensure to mask and protect important polygon flow regions, such as the eyes and

80
00:06:51.340 --> 00:06:57.220
inside of the mouth, when projecting details onto the conformed mesh.

81
